ADDIS ABABA, Ethiopia, June 2, 2020/APO Group/ --
                                                        
                            The total laboratory tests conducted within 24 hours are 3,932; of these eighty-seven (87) of them are confirmed positive for COVID-19 and the total confirmed cases as of today are 1,344. Among the confirmed cases, 59 of them are male and 28 are female and their age ranges front 10 to 70 years. All of the confirmed cases are Ethiopians. Among the cases, sixty-seven (67) of them are identified from Addis Ababa, two (2) from Tigray region, six (6) from Oromia region, seven (7) from Amhara region, one (1) from Harari region and four (4) from Somali region.



The potential sources of exposure of the confirmed cases are presented below:




	
		
			
